-IaaS? (Infrastructure as a Service?)
-DBaaS? (DataBase as a Service?)
-CaaS? (Code as a Service?)

Make sure the company you are paying for your email services has been Audited by a well known company (then you know you could avoid 80% of the dangers out there). Learn the best security practices for your systems too because a lot of the times we get compromised by our own mistakes. Make sure there is encryption for privacy and even better, a decentralized service.
Make sure you have a list of your needs, a list of future needs and a list with all the possible email services. With the first two you can find the third.

Some tips for defining the best host for your emails:
 First of all, know what you need.
 Secondly, do a thorough research on the current providers and their plans
 Thirdly, find the plan that suits you the most without overspending in unused services.
 Make sure you security is not compromised.
 Happy mailing!
